1
00:00:01,585 --> 00:00:03,044
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "ENTERPRISE"...</i>

2
00:00:03,044 --> 00:00:05,005
YOU, DENOBULAN.
COME WITH US.

3
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,967
[ GRUNTING ]

4
00:00:07,967 --> 00:00:10,093
THE VIRUS IS SPREADING
FROM PLANET TO PLANET.

5
00:00:10,093 --> 00:00:13,388
-MILLIONS ARE ALREADY INFECTED.
-WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH ME?

6
00:00:13,388 --> 00:00:17,017
IF THIS CONTINUES, THE KLINGON
SPECIES WILL CEASE TO EXIST.

7
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:19,770
THERE'S A JOB
THAT NEEDS DOING, LIEUTENANT.

8
00:00:19,770 --> 00:00:22,356
IT MAY BE THE ONLY WAY
TO SAVE YOUR FRIEND'S LIFE.

9
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:24,191
YOU DON'T SERIOUSLY EXPECT ME

10
00:00:24,191 --> 00:00:26,568
TO HELP YOU CREATE
KLINGON AUGMENTS?

11
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:27,778
TAKE HIM.

12
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:31,866
THE MALCOLM REED I KNOW
WOULD GIVE HIS LIFE

13
00:00:31,866 --> 00:00:33,033
BEFORE COMMITTING TREASON.

14
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:36,370
THERE ARE SOME...OBLIGATIONS...

15
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:38,956
THAT GO BEYOND
MY LOYALTY TO YOU

16
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:40,332
AND THIS CREW.

17
00:00:40,332 --> 00:00:41,876
-T'Pol to Captain Archer.
-Go ahead.

18
00:00:41,876 --> 00:00:44,336
The warp matrix
has been compromised

19
00:00:44,336 --> 00:00:45,796
by a Klingon subroutine.

20
00:00:45,796 --> 00:00:48,382
IT'S INFILTRATED
OUR COMMAND PROTOCOLS.

21
00:00:48,382 --> 00:00:49,925
PRESSURE'S INCREASING AGAIN.

22
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:51,552
TAKE US TO WARP 5.2.

23
00:00:51,552 --> 00:00:53,554
SIR, WE CAN'T HOLD
THAT SPEED FOR LONG.

24
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:57,016
We're out of options, Travis.
5.2.

25
00:00:57,016 --> 00:00:59,142
<i>AND NOW THE CONCLUSION.</i>

26
00:01:06,025 --> 00:01:07,693
[ RUMBLING ]

27
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:16,493
WE HAVE 47 MINUTES
UNTIL OUR REACTOR BREACHES.

28
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:18,453
WHAT DID THE KLINGONS DO TO IT?

29
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:20,664
THEY ALTERED OUR
ENGINEERING SUBROUTINES.

30
00:01:20,664 --> 00:01:24,376
IF WE GO BELOW WARP 5,
THE REACTOR'S GOING TO EXPLODE.

31
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:25,711
HOW CAN I HELP?

32
00:01:25,711 --> 00:01:27,713
I'VE JUST BEEN TALKING
WITH TRIP.

33
00:01:27,713 --> 00:01:29,882
<i>COLUMBIA</i> CAN RENDEZVOUS
WITH US IN 30 MINUTES.

34
00:01:29,882 --> 00:01:31,800
HE SAYS HE CAN
RESTORE THE SUBROUTINES.

35
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,635
HE CAN'T DO THAT
FROM<i> COLUMBIA.</i>

36
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:35,220
WE'RE GONNA BRING HIM ONBOARD.

37
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:36,847
THE TRANSPORTER
WON'T OPERATE AT WARP,

38
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:38,473
AND DOCKING'S OUT
OF THE QUESTION.

39
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,141
TRIP TOLD ME
YOU HAVE EXPERIENCE

40
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:42,101
TRANSFERRING PERSONNEL
AT WARP SPEED.

41
00:01:42,101 --> 00:01:45,940
IN TRAINING EXERCISES, YES,
BUT AT WARP SPEED 1.

42
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:48,358
EVERY MOVE WAS REHEARSED
IN SIMULATORS FOR WEEKS.

43
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:50,611
WE DON'T HAVE WEEKS.

44
00:01:50,611 --> 00:01:53,530
WE'LL HAVE TO MERGE OUR
WARP FIELD WITH<i> COLUMBIA'S.</i>

45
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:55,908
T'POL'S DOING
THE CALCULATIONS NOW.

46
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:59,453
AT WARP 5, WE'LL HAVE TO MOVE
WITHIN 50 METERS OF EACH OTHER.

47
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:01,997
HAS ANYONE
EVER DONE THIS BEFORE?

48
00:02:02,998 --> 00:02:06,835
TRAVIS CAN HANDLE THE FLYING.

49
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:09,046
CAN YOU GET TRIP OVER HERE?

50
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:11,757
[ RUMBLING ]

51
00:02:11,757 --> 00:02:14,134
YOU'LL HAVE TO LET ME OUT
OF THIS BRIG.

52
00:02:17,888 --> 00:02:22,684
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

53
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:25,771
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

54
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:29,817
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

55
00:02:29,817 --> 00:02:33,445
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

56
00:02:33,445 --> 00:02:37,825
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

57
00:02:37,825 --> 00:02:41,328
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

58
00:02:41,328 --> 00:02:45,499
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

59
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:48,376
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

60
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:51,254
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

61
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:53,298
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

62
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,384
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

63
00:02:56,384 --> 00:03:01,556
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

64
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:04,309
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

65
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:08,105
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

66
00:03:08,105 --> 00:03:11,733
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

67
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:17,405
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

68
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:19,491
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

69
00:03:19,491 --> 00:03:21,576
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

70
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:25,497
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

71
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:29,835
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

72
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:53,567
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-COMMANDER TUCKER.

73
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,403
Are you ready for this?

74
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:58,613
AS READY AS I'LL EVER BE.

75
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:02,534
OPEN A CHANNEL.

76
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:04,828
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
<i>Columbia</i> to<i> Enterprise.</i>

77
00:04:04,828 --> 00:04:06,454
THIS IS ARCHER.

78
00:04:06,454 --> 00:04:09,374
We're matching speed
and trajectory as requested.

79
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,418
STAND BY,<i> COLUMBIA.</i>

80
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:12,460
ARCHER TO REED.

81
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,796
GO AHEAD.

82
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:16,464
We're in position.

83
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:24,056
HAVE THEM START
THEIR ROTATION.

84
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,570
COMING UP ON 100 METERS.

85
00:04:38,570 --> 00:04:42,657
90. 80 METERS.

86
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:44,076
THIS IS THE BRIDGE.

87
00:04:44,076 --> 00:04:47,037
ALL HANDS BRACE FOR
WARP-FIELD CONTACT.

88
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:59,049
HOLD HER STEADY, TRAVIS,

89
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:02,052
or Chef will know who to blame
for the mess in the galley.

90
00:05:03,637 --> 00:05:06,098
WE'RE AT 50 METERS
AND HOLDING.

91
00:05:06,098 --> 00:05:08,308
MAKE SURE EVERYTHING'S READY
FOR TRIP IN ENGINEERING.

92
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:13,521
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

93
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:16,608
-ARCHER TO REED.
YOU'RE ALL CLEAR.
-Understood.

94
00:05:16,608 --> 00:05:20,904
<i>COLUMBIA,</i>
I'M DEPLOYING THE TETHER.

95
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:32,166
NICE SHOOTING, MALCOLM.

96
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,629
TUCKER TO CAPTAIN HERNANDEZ.

97
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,214
-Go ahead.
-I'M HEADING OUT.

98
00:05:39,214 --> 00:05:41,216
Quick as you can, Commander.

99
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:42,467
[ SIGHS ]

100
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:58,317
NEVER THOUGHT I'D SEE
THE STARS LIKE THIS.

101
00:05:58,317 --> 00:06:00,359
EYES ON THE CABLE, COMMANDER.

102
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,154
I NEED YOU BACK HERE
IN ONE PIECE.

103
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,752
YOU'RE DOING FINE, TRIP.

104
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:19,171
[ RUMBLING ]

105
00:06:19,171 --> 00:06:21,048
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

106
00:06:21,048 --> 00:06:22,757
T'POL, WHAT'S HAPPENING?

107
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:24,425
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

108
00:06:24,425 --> 00:06:27,595
I'M READING A FLUCTUATION
IN THE WARP FIELD.

109
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:29,514
Take power from life support
if you have to,

110
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:30,557
BUT KEEP THE FIELD CONSTANT.

111
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:32,267
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

112
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:35,729
SIR, I'M HAVING TROUBLE
HOLDING POSITION.

113
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:38,690
52 METERS, 55.

114
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:40,650
DON'T MEAN TO BE A PEST,

115
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,361
BUT COULD SOMEONE TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?

116
00:06:42,361 --> 00:06:45,613
YOU'RE ALMOST HERE, TRIP.
KEEP GOING.

117
00:06:45,613 --> 00:06:46,948
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

118
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:49,117
ENGINEERING, REPORT!

119
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,870
I'M REROUTING POWER NOW,
CAPTAIN. STAND BY.

120
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:54,873
59 METERS.

121
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,341
THE TETHER'S AT ITS LIMIT!
HURRY UP!

122
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:08,053
T'POL TO THE BRIDGE.
IT'S NOT WORKING.

123
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:09,763
THE FIELD IS STILL
FLUCTUATING.

124
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:12,307
ALMOST THERE!

125
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,836
PERMISSION TO COME ABOARD?

126
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:49,970
BRIDGE, I HAVE HIM.

127
00:07:52,431 --> 00:07:53,807
YOU ALL RIGHT, TRIP?

128
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:56,435
I'LL FEEL A LOT BETTER
WHEN THIS IS OVER.

129
00:07:56,435 --> 00:07:59,604
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY TO DO THIS,
CAPTAIN -- A COLD START.

130
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:02,523
I HAVE TO SHUT DOWN THE REACTOR
AND RESET THE ALGORITHMS.

131
00:08:02,523 --> 00:08:04,818
ONCE WE BRING
THE WARP ENGINE BACK ONLINE,

132
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:07,028
THE SUBROUTINES SHOULD BE
BACK TO NORMAL.

133
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:09,197
BUT IF WE SHUT DOWN
THE REACTOR --

134
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:11,116
That's why we need to move
inside<i> Columbia's</i> warp field.

135
00:08:11,116 --> 00:08:14,244
THEY CAN SUSTAIN OUR SPEED WHILE
I REINITIALIZE THE ENGINES.

136
00:08:14,244 --> 00:08:16,246
THEY WON'T BE ABLE TO HOLD US
FOR MORE THAN A MINUTE OR TWO.

137
00:08:16,246 --> 00:08:17,622
THEY DON'T HAVE ENOUGH POWER.

138
00:08:17,622 --> 00:08:19,040
I'VE GOT A SHORTCUT IN MIND.

139
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,168
SHORTCUT?

140
00:08:21,168 --> 00:08:22,961
THOSE SUBROUTINES
WOULD TAKE HOURS TO DECRYPT.

141
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:25,297
BETTER JUST TO PURGE THEM,
WIPE THEM CLEAN.

142
00:08:27,466 --> 00:08:28,842
I'LL CONTACT<i> COLUMBIA.</i>

143
00:08:37,434 --> 00:08:39,102
WHAT ARE THEY HERE FOR?

144
00:08:39,102 --> 00:08:41,896
THE CAPTAIN AND I HAVE HAD
A SLIGHT MISUNDERSTANDING.

145
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:43,690
HOW SLIGHT?

146
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:45,817
THESE GENTLEMEN ARE HERE
TO ESCORT ME BACK TO THE BRIG.

147
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:47,819
DON'T WORRY.

148
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:50,613
I'LL TELL YOU ALL ABOUT IT
WHEN WE'RE NOT QUITE SO BUSY.

149
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:56,870
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

150
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,621
FANCY MEETING YOU HERE.

151
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:00,623
INTERMIX PRESSURE?

152
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,542
1527.

153
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:05,337
-FIELD VARIANCE?
-87 MILLICOCHRANES.

154
00:09:05,337 --> 00:09:08,256
SOMEBODY HASN'T BEEN TAKING
VERY GOOD CARE OF MY ENGINE.

155
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:10,925
SPEAK WITH THE KLINGONS.

156
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:13,636
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
-YOU MIGHT WANT TO TAKE NOTES.

157
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,389
I'M ABOUT TO PERFORM
A MANUAL SHUTDOWN AND RESTART

158
00:09:15,389 --> 00:09:16,515
IN LESS THAN TWO MINUTES.

159
00:09:16,515 --> 00:09:17,598
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

160
00:09:17,598 --> 00:09:19,226
WATCH ME.

161
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:25,773
<i>-COLUMBIA</i> TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i> 
-GO AHEAD.

162
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:28,068
I've routed everything I've got
to my warp field.

163
00:09:28,068 --> 00:09:29,610
DO ME A FAVOR, JONATHAN.

164
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,946
MAKE THIS QUICK.

165
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:38,661
ARCHER TO TRIP.

166
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:41,415
READY WHEN YOU ARE.

167
00:09:41,415 --> 00:09:44,167
STAND BY! EVERYONE GET AWAY
FROM THE BULKHEADS!

168
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:46,627
IT'S GONNA GET
A LITTLE HOT IN HERE!

169
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:49,797
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

170
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:54,511
REACTOR SHUT DOWN IN 5, 4,

171
00:09:54,511 --> 00:09:57,472
3, 2, 1!

172
00:10:04,979 --> 00:10:06,731
T'POL, PRIME THE INJECTORS.

173
00:10:06,731 --> 00:10:08,775
-JENKINS, MAN THE RELAYS.
-YES, SIR.

174
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:19,411
<i>COLUMBIA</i> TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>
YOU'VE GOT ABOUT 40 SECONDS.

175
00:10:20,579 --> 00:10:23,164
UNDERSTOOD.

176
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:25,125
-[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
-Trip, how's it going?

177
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:28,169
-JUST ANOTHER MINUTE, CAPTAIN.
-You don't have a minute!

178
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:30,589
GET READY TO INITIALIZE
THE MATRIX.

179
00:10:39,097 --> 00:10:41,558
<i>ENTERPRISE,</i>
WE'RE LOSING THE FIELD.

180
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:45,770
15 SECONDS, TRIP.

181
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:48,398
ALMOST THERE.
FULL POWER TO CONTAINMENT.

182
00:10:48,398 --> 00:10:50,066
FIRE UP THE ANTIMATTER STREAM.

183
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,067
10 seconds.

184
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,861
9, 8, 7, 6...

185
00:10:53,861 --> 00:10:56,823
-COMMANDER!
-HERE WE GO!
-...5, 4...

186
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:58,866
3, 2...

187
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:01,702
[ ENGINES WHOOSH ]

188
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,170
WE'VE GOT WARP POWER.

189
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:13,173
ENGINEERING TO THE BRIDGE.

190
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:15,716
SUBROUTINES HAVE BEEN PURGED.

191
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:18,011
Appreciate the house call,
Mr. Tucker.

192
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:19,762
ANYTIME.

193
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:22,723
I'D LIKE TO DROP TO IMPULSE
FOR A WHILE, CAPTAIN,

194
00:11:22,723 --> 00:11:25,185
-just to check things over.
-STAND BY.

195
00:11:25,185 --> 00:11:29,897
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> TO<i> COLUMBIA.</i> 
THANKS FOR THE LIFT.

196
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:33,485
YOU'RE NOT GETTING AWAY WITH
MY CHIEF ENGINEER THAT EASILY.

197
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,156
ANY PLANS FOR THE NEXT FEW DAYS?

198
00:11:38,156 --> 00:11:40,699
WHAT'VE YOU GOT IN MIND?

199
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:53,838
PHLOX.

200
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:56,007
PHLOX?

201
00:11:59,718 --> 00:12:01,804
THIS WILL HELP.

202
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:04,015
[ GRUNTS ]

203
00:12:04,015 --> 00:12:06,685
MY APOLOGIES
FOR THE GENERAL'S CONDUCT.

204
00:12:06,685 --> 00:12:09,187
SO CRUEL! THIS IS NO WAY
TO TREAT A MAN OF SCIENCE!

205
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:12,524
[ PANTING ]

206
00:12:12,524 --> 00:12:13,900
THEN END IT.

207
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,069
CONTACT STARFLEET.

208
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:17,820
MY PEOPLE NEED YOU, PHLOX.

209
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:20,532
WE HAVE NO HEALERS
WITH YOUR ABILITIES.

210
00:12:20,532 --> 00:12:24,202
YOU WANT ME TO CREATE
KLINGON AUGMENTS,

211
00:12:24,202 --> 00:12:25,704
LIVING WEAPONS.

212
00:12:25,704 --> 00:12:27,247
I WON'T DO IT.

213
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:30,041
NO, NO.
I'VE BEEN REVIEWING YOUR WORK.

214
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:31,834
IT'S BRILLIANT!

215
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:36,423
YOU HAVE DISCOVERED A WEAKNESS
IN THE VIRUS CAUSING THE PLAGUE.

216
00:12:36,423 --> 00:12:40,218
IF WE INTERRUPT THE
TRANSCRIPTION SEQUENCE HERE...

217
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:49,810
YES. YES.

218
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:54,357
THAT WOULD STOP
THE GENETIC EFFECTS

219
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:56,359
OF THE VIRUS IN STAGE ONE.

220
00:12:56,359 --> 00:12:58,403
THERE'D BE CHANGES
OF APPEARANCE,

221
00:12:58,403 --> 00:13:00,405
SOME MINOR NEURAL REORDERING,

222
00:13:00,405 --> 00:13:03,908
BUT NO DEVELOPMENT
OF STAGE-TWO CHARACTERISTICS.

223
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:07,161
NO ENHANCED STRENGTH
OR SPEED OR ENDURANCE.

224
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:08,829
[ CHUCKLES ]

225
00:13:11,374 --> 00:13:16,296
BUT THEN GENERAL K'VAGH
WOULD NOT GET HIS AUGMENTS.

226
00:13:16,296 --> 00:13:18,256
HE WOULD NEVER ALLOW IT.

227
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:22,885
WHAT IF WE DON'T TELL HIM?

228
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,887
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT WILL HAPPEN

229
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:27,890
IF THE GENERAL LEARNS
THAT WE'VE DECEIVED HIM?

230
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:32,061
THE CURE WOULD SAVE
MILLIONS OF INNOCENT LIVES.

231
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:36,107
WHAT MORE HONORABLE DEATH
COULD THERE BE FOR A HEALER,

232
00:13:36,107 --> 00:13:39,277
KLINGON OR DENOBULAN?

233
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:45,908
CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

234
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:49,203
I'VE ASKED<i> COLUMBIA</i> TO JOIN US
IN OUR SEARCH FOR PHLOX.

235
00:13:49,203 --> 00:13:50,789
WE'LL HAVE A BETTER CHANCE

236
00:13:50,789 --> 00:13:53,040
OF MAKING IT
THROUGH KLINGON TERRITORY

237
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,875
WITH TWICE THE FIREPOWER.

238
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:58,837
I DON'T SUPPOSE YOU CAN TELL ME
WHERE I'M GOING THIS TIME?

239
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:01,299
NO, I DIDN'T THINK SO.

240
00:14:04,636 --> 00:14:07,013
THOSE ARE MY PERSONAL FILES.

241
00:14:07,013 --> 00:14:09,098
NOT WHEN THEY AFFECT MY SHIP!

242
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:15,605
T'POL RESTORED EVERYTHING
YOU TRIED TO ERASE.

243
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:24,113
WE RAN HIS FACE AND VOICEPRINT
THROUGH OUR DATABASE.

244
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:26,157
HIS NAME'S HARRIS.

245
00:14:26,157 --> 00:14:30,453
HE WORKED IN STARFLEET SECURITY
UP TILL FIVE YEARS AGO.

246
00:14:30,453 --> 00:14:31,996
AFTER THAT, HIS FILE ENDS.

247
00:14:31,996 --> 00:14:34,999
CAPTAIN, THERE'S NOTHING MORE
I CAN ADD.

248
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:36,543
I WON'T ACCEPT THAT!

249
00:14:36,543 --> 00:14:38,837
YOU ENDANGERED
EVERY MEMBER OF THIS CREW.

250
00:14:38,837 --> 00:14:41,005
YOU ANSWER TO<i> ME.</i>

251
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:46,594
I THOUGHT I KNEW YOU, MALCOLM.

252
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:52,684
WHATEVER HOLD THIS HARRIS HAS
ON YOU,

253
00:14:52,684 --> 00:14:55,061
-YOU COULD'VE COME TO ME.
-I'M UNDER ORDERS.

254
00:14:55,061 --> 00:14:58,606
I'M YOUR COMMANDING OFFICER!

255
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:01,776
IF YOU DON'T TELL ME WHAT'S
GOING ON, I'LL GO TO STARFLEET.

256
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:04,237
WHATEVER YOU THINK YOU'VE BEEN
TRYING TO KEEP HIDDEN

257
00:15:04,237 --> 00:15:06,072
IS GOING TO COME OUT --
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

258
00:15:06,072 --> 00:15:09,075
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

259
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:12,203
I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT I DON'T KNOW.

260
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:18,334
THEN LET ME TALK
TO SOMEONE WHO CAN.

261
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:22,630
SEND A MESSAGE TO HARRIS.

262
00:15:28,553 --> 00:15:31,389
HAS THE HOUSE OF PHLOX
ALWAYS BEEN ONE OF HEALERS?

263
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:36,060
THERE IS NO, UH,
HOUSE OF PHLOX.

264
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:39,021
DENOBULAN FAMILY UNITS
ARE DIFFERENT FROM KLINGONS'.

265
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:42,275
AH, YES, I'VE HEARD.

266
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:44,360
THREE WIVES FOR EACH HUSBAND.

267
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,112
THREE HUSBANDS FOR EACH WIFE.

268
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:50,199
YOUR MATING PRACTICES
MUST BE VERY COMPLEX.

269
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:52,285
WONDROUSLY SO.

270
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:54,161
WHAT ABOUT THE HOUSE OF ANTAAK?

271
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:57,457
WE ARE A WARRIOR CASTE.

272
00:15:57,457 --> 00:16:01,669
WHEN I BECAME A HEALER,
MY FATHER DISOWNED ME.

273
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:04,046
AS A PHYSICIAN
IN THE IMPERIAL FLEET,

274
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,590
YOU'VE SERVED IN THE MILITARY.

275
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:08,008
NOT AS WELL AS I SHOULD HAVE.

276
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:15,809
